<paragraph id="9667CBE218E745AE317FA66EEBE2B1EA" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E91FDED80E6EFE3F798B89D2F8704016" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName id="E74DF25F4E9717DAF17049BBD3936203" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Riopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Riopa davidii" order="Polyporales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="davidii">Riopa davidii</taxonomicName>
D. A. Reid (= 
<taxonomicName id="E26D05FA1F5F6F9915127B39F4658875" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Riopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Riopa metamorphosa" order="Polyporales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="metamorphosa">Riopa metamorphosa</taxonomicName>
(Fuckel) Miettinen &amp; Spirin).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CCA69A31B9A9B9EF79B28476FEA911AD" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="description">
<paragraph id="64441D64B39FCA8B3D109C72838E0CB1" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C85BB3C91342A47D288A4D06DB30914A" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
White, resupinate polypores with shallow pores, 2-5 per mm. Hyphal structure monomitic, clamps absent. Hyphae thin- to slightly thick-walled, similar throughout the basidiocarp, hyphae not swollen, wider (3-5 
<normalizedToken id="AFAB386DB1B8A6702C384FECA849ABB2" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
in diameter) in subiculum, a bit narrower in trama (2.8-3.5 
<normalizedToken id="E413E38F815016BD8A6CDE0D732144D1" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
). Hymenial branching corymb-like. Thin-walled, poorly differentiated hymenial cystidia and conidia in one species. Spores curved cylindrical, sausage-like, thin-walled, mid-sized (4.5
<normalizedToken id="F9078AD8CF52AED070711C290E251CD6" originalValue="–6.5×2–">-6.5x2-</normalizedToken>
3 
<normalizedToken id="0C77DFCE56C56CAD8D5B7AEC76AA4B03" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0549751BB2BC60AD91380ADFF484586A" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="F568EB13BC86CC74970E23EC423381A7" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="01373162B9DFA935F96D62DB7A0FD3DF" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<bibRefCitation id="6B8B51E95A8C3764663CC142645EC3E1" author="Reid, DA" journalOrPublisher="Revue de Mycologie" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="237 - 267" title="Spring fungi in Corsica." volume="33" year="1969">Reid (1969)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="56D85219F2EED1FB10A23D825803A601" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Riopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Riopa" order="Polyporales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Riopa</taxonomicName>
as a monotypic genus with 
<taxonomicName id="6FA601EEAC359D1FAA43862A4A50ADA0" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Riopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Riopa davidii" order="Polyporales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="davidii">Riopa davidii</taxonomicName>
D. A. Reid from Corsica as the sole species. 
<bibRefCitation id="88E87DBE7E9AFB6F536DE0C6844B7B4A" author="Ryvarden, L" journalOrPublisher="Synopsis Fungorum" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="1 - 363" title="Genera of polypores. Nomenclature and taxonomy." volume="5" year="1991">Ryvarden (1991)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="38FD63F0F355646F5F2349AD9047CF5F" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Riopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Riopa davidii" order="Polyporales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="davidii">Riopa davidii</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="319A21844D617F7C49607AC69CD92224" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phanerochaetaceae" genus="Ceriporia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ceriporia camaresiana" order="Polyporales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="camaresiana">Ceriporia camaresiana</taxonomicName>
(Bourdot &amp; Galzin) Bondartsev &amp; Singer, in effect making 
<taxonomicName id="3A4BFA28A36A1DB44380B94F18AE4AF8" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Riopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Riopa" order="Polyporales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Riopa</taxonomicName>
a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="FCD8A02BDF6F449C4C13EFFCC0522D01" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phanerochaetaceae" genus="Ceriporia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ceriporia" order="Polyporales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Ceriporia</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="4844F9F96BF24CAAFD136E91FC0D6120" author="Pieri, M" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe Mycologique de France" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="193 - 250" title="À propos du genre Ceriporia Donk (Aphyllophoromycetidae)." volume="113" year="1997">Pieri and Rivoire (1997)</bibRefCitation>
regarded 
<taxonomicName id="46F0397B23CF4C825F5EA6E63F45DB62" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Riopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Riopa davidii" order="Polyporales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="davidii">Riopa davidii</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="45D7B4DA7360F068D6129BEA23FB21AE" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phanerochaetaceae" genus="Ceriporia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ceriporia camaresiana" order="Polyporales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="camaresiana">Ceriporia camaresiana</taxonomicName>
as separate species, and made the combination 
<taxonomicName id="020D543796E44170749FEBD837EAF2C0" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phanerochaetaceae" genus="Ceriporia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ceriporia davidii" order="Polyporales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="davidii">Ceriporia davidii</taxonomicName>
. Their concept of the species was mixed, as can be seen already from the spore variation they report. Their specimens from mainland France did seem to represent a species of 
<taxonomicName id="BC4706C3392C95D0B0866AC88B15B8D7" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phanerochaetaceae" genus="Ceriporia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ceriporia" order="Polyporales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Ceriporia</taxonomicName>
separate from 
<taxonomicName id="EE36C9F2D27B77BD510F2D139945F67A" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phanerochaetaceae" genus="Ceriporia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ceriporia camaresiana" order="Polyporales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="camaresiana">Ceriporia camaresiana</taxonomicName>
, and consequently 
<taxonomicName id="7D277431CA32599EC366C4268E4E8A9A" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phanerochaetaceae" genus="Ceriporia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ceriporia davidii" order="Polyporales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="davidii">Ceriporia davidii</taxonomicName>
was adopted by 
<bibRefCitation id="29CE854E648E13CE41ACF10DE5F16D0C" author="Bernicchia, A" journalOrPublisher="Candusso, Alassio" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" title="Polyporaceae s. l." year="2005">Bernicchia (2005)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="2F8C417670E4B58056E61A839E9464A0" author="Ryvarden, L" journalOrPublisher="Fungiflora, Oslo" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" title="Poroid fungi of Europe." year="2014">Ryvarden and Melo (2014)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="610A03545062D5589EBBE15365A7D498" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
We studied the type of 
<taxonomicName id="03B191E9E16EEF18947730D82649A2F7" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Riopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Riopa davidii" order="Polyporales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="davidii">Riopa davidii</taxonomicName>
, and it turned out to be a more recent synonym for 
<taxonomicName id="DE08E33CEE92FFF8B0F4AC280C9D7F2D" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phanerochaetaceae" genus="Ceriporia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ceriporia metamorphosa" order="Polyporales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="metamorphosa">Ceriporia metamorphosa</taxonomicName>
(Fuckel) Ryvarden &amp; Gilb. After studying the French material of 
<taxonomicName id="CC3638E6DD2BB8D0C201D1C5BB700C14" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phanerochaetaceae" genus="Ceriporia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ceriporia davidii" order="Polyporales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="davidii">Ceriporia davidii</taxonomicName>
collected by B. Rivoire, we could also conclude that 
<taxonomicName id="F036AFC3D49B5E6E4DB224BED83ACE59" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phanerochaetaceae" genus="Ceriporia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ceriporia davidii" order="Polyporales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="davidii">Ceriporia davidii</taxonomicName>
sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="89F8D4D8E16ED5F04650252D57E9377D" author="Pieri, M" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe Mycologique de France" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="193 - 250" title="À propos du genre Ceriporia Donk (Aphyllophoromycetidae)." volume="113" year="1997">Pieri and Rivoire (1997)</bibRefCitation>
needs to be described with a new name (
<taxonomicName id="D99C9C8F2C87175E209F42C2066D2624" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phanerochaetaceae" genus="Ceriporia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ceriporia pierii" order="Polyporales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="pierii">Ceriporia pierii</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4888AF81C6F0B60359236B3B8EAC6837" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phanerochaetaceae" genus="Ceriporia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ceriporia pierii" order="Polyporales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="pierii">Ceriporia pierii</taxonomicName>
and also 
<taxonomicName id="68D6A5C4E8642BA5722AC9FABF9589E0" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phanerochaetaceae" genus="Ceriporia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ceriporia camaresiana" order="Polyporales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="camaresiana">Ceriporia camaresiana</taxonomicName>
belong to the 
<taxonomicName id="ABC7E98F4274ADF747CD658615E03D38" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phanerochaetaceae" genus="Ceriporia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ceriporia" order="Polyporales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Ceriporia</taxonomicName>
clade and are only distantly related to 
<taxonomicName id="978EB44D89B51745651DB14606F867B2" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Riopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Riopa" order="Polyporales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Riopa</taxonomicName>
(Figure 2).
</paragraph>
